Put the @Toulouse sausages{4} on a foil lined #baking tray{}. Grill until cooked, ~{15-20%minutes}, turning halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Halve, peel and finely slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and finely sliced). Add to the pan with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Strip the @rosemary{4} leaves from their stalks. Finely chop the leaves (discard the stalks). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%packet} in a #sieve{}. Cut the @ciabatta{1} in half (as if you were going to make a sandwich).

Stir the rosemary and @punchy balsamic mustard{1} into the onion for ~{1%minute}. Add the @water{100%ml} and @red wine stock paste{14} stock paste. Bring to the boil, stirring to dissolve the stock paste, then add the @baby spinach{125%g}. Cover with a #lid{} and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes} then stir in the lentils and cook for a further ~{3%minutes}.

Three mins before the sausages are done, pop the ciabatta on the #tray{} (drain off any liquid on the tray first), cut side up, drizzle with a little @oil{} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}. Return to the grill until the sausages are cooked and the ciabatta toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper, if needed.

Serve the balsamic lentils in #bowls{} topped with the sausages and ciabatta. ENJOY!